---
import Canvas from "../layouts/Canvas.astro";
---

<Canvas title="18 · CI/CD — Sardis Canvas" currentId="cicd">

<section class="hero">
        <span class="eyebrow">Canvas 18 · Ops</span>
        <h1>CI / CD</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          Twenty-five GitHub Actions workflows guard the repo. Four classes: tests on every PR,
          security scans on every push and weekly, deploys on merge to <code>main</code>, publishes on tag.
          One branch is production (<code>main</code>). Everything else is preview.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section" style="padding-top:0; border-top:0;">
        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <span class="callout-title">TL;DR</span>
          <code>main</code> is the only long-lived branch. Every PR runs the full CI matrix (Python,
          contracts, TS SDK, and landing) plus security. Merge to <code>main</code> triggers
          path-scoped deploys: API → Cloud Run <code>us-east1</code>, Landing → Vercel.
          Releases to PyPI and npm fire on version tags. Uptime pings every 10 minutes.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Overview -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Overview</div>
          <h2>Branch strategy and gating.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            The default branch is <code>main</code>. PRs against it run the CI and security suites but
            do not publish. Merges to <code>main</code> trigger the deploy workflows that match changed
            paths — only the pieces that actually changed redeploy.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">What runs on a PR</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>ci.yml</code> (Python lint+test, contracts strict + gas, TS SDK,
              landing build), <code>test-api.yml</code> (sardis-api scoped tests), <code>codeql.yml</code>
              (Python + JS/TS), <code>secret-scan.yml</code> (gitleaks), <code>security-scan.yml</code>
              (pip-audit + Trivy + Bandit), <code>fuzz.yml</code> (atheris against spending_policy).
              Path filters skip irrelevant workflows.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">What runs on merge to main</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>deploy-api-cloudrun.yml</code>, <code>deploy-landing.yml</code>,
              <code>deploy.yml</code> — each gated by a
              <code>paths:</code> filter so a docs-only merge doesn't redeploy the API. Verification step
              (<code>curl /health</code>) runs after each Cloud Run deploy.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">What runs on a version tag</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>release-python-sdk.yml</code> (PyPI / TestPyPI — <code>py-sdk-v*</code>),
              <code>release-python-integrations.yml</code> (batch publish for langchain/crewai/adk/agent-sdk/connect),
              <code>release-npm.yml</code> (<code>mcp-v*</code>, <code>sdk-js-v*</code>, <code>ai-sdk-v*</code>,
              <code>connect-js-v*</code>), <code>publish.yml</code>, <code>sign-artifacts.yml</code>.
              Each verifies pyproject/package.json version matches the tag, runs tests, builds, publishes,
              then smoke-installs from the registry.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">What runs on a schedule</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>monitoring.yml</code> every 10 min (synthetic <code>/health</code> probe +
              Slack notify on failure); <code>uptime*.yml</code> (<code>uptime</code>,
              <code>uptime-response-time</code>, <code>uptime-graphs</code>, <code>uptime-static-site</code>,
              <code>uptime-summary</code>); <code>nightly-sandbox-e2e.yml</code> 04:20 UTC;
              <code>codeql.yml</code> weekly Monday; <code>scorecard.yml</code> weekly Monday;
              <code>fuzz.yml</code> weekly Saturday.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Pipeline diagram -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Pipeline</div>
          <h2>PR → preview → production.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Simplified view. Not every workflow is shown — see the tables below for full coverage.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram">
          <pre class="mermaid" is:raw>
flowchart LR
    Dev[Developer branch] --> PR[PR against main]
    PR --> CI[ci.yml + test-api.yml]
    PR --> Sec[codeql · secret-scan · security-scan · fuzz]
    PR --> PrevVercel[Vercel preview URLs]
    CI --> Gate{All green?}
    Sec --> Gate
    Gate -- no --> Dev
    Gate -- yes --> Merge[Merge to main]
    Merge --> PathFilter{paths: changed?}
    PathFilter -- sardis-api --> Cloudbuild[Cloud Build]
    Cloudbuild --> CloudRun[Cloud Run · us-east1]
    CloudRun --> HealthCheck[curl /health]
    PathFilter -- apps/landing --> VercelLand[Vercel · sardis.sh]
    Tag[Version tag py-sdk-v* / sdk-js-v* / ...] --> ReleaseMatrix[release-python-sdk · release-npm · release-python-integrations]
    ReleaseMatrix --> Registry[PyPI · npm]
    Registry --> Smoke[Smoke install from registry]
          </pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- CI workflows -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">CI</div>
          <h2>Test workflows.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Workflow</th><th>Trigger</th><th>Jobs</th><th>What it proves</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>ci.yml</code></td>
              <td>push main · PR</td>
              <td>python-lint-test · idempotency-replay-e2e · contracts-gas · contracts-strict · typescript-sdk · build-landing</td>
              <td>ruff + pytest with <code>--cov-fail-under=40</code> on core/api, forge gas ceiling and full strict test suite (solc 0.8.24 pinned), TS SDK + MCP build and tests, landing typecheck + build.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>test-api.yml</code></td>
              <td>push main · PR (scoped to <code>sardis-api/</code> and <code>sardis-core/</code>)</td>
              <td>API Lint &amp; Test</td>
              <td>Faster feedback loop for API changes: ruff + pytest on api/core with <code>SARDIS_ENVIRONMENT=dev</code>.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>ci-integrations.yml</code></td>
              <td>push main · PR</td>
              <td>per-framework integration builds</td>
              <td>Validates that every framework SDK in <code>packages/sardis-*</code> still builds and imports.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>idempotency-replay gate (in <code>ci.yml</code>)</td>
              <td>PR</td>
              <td>E2E script <code>scripts/release/idempotency_replay_e2e_check.sh</code></td>
              <td>Confirms the Phase-3 dedup store and replay cache still refuse to double-execute a payment.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Security workflows -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Security</div>
          <h2>Scans and attestations.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Every workflow pins actions by commit SHA, not tag. Default permissions are empty
            (<code>permissions: &#123;&#125;</code>) and each job declares the minimum it needs.
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Workflow</th><th>Trigger</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>codeql.yml</code></td><td>push · PR · weekly Mon 05:30 UTC</td><td>CodeQL on Python and JavaScript/TypeScript. Uploads SARIF to GitHub Security.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>secret-scan.yml</code></td><td>push · PR</td><td>gitleaks full-history scan (<code>fetch-depth: 0</code>). Fails the run on any detection.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>security-scan.yml</code></td><td>push · PR · weekly Mon 06:00 UTC</td><td>Three jobs: <code>pip-audit</code> (Python deps), Trivy container scan of the built API image (fails on CRITICAL/HIGH, <code>ignore-unfixed</code>), Bandit SAST on <code>sardis/</code> + <code>packages/sardis-api/src</code> + <code>packages/sardis-core/src</code>.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>scorecard.yml</code></td><td>push · weekly Mon 06:00 UTC</td><td>OpenSSF Scorecard → SARIF → uploaded to GitHub Security. Tracks branch protection, token permissions, pinned deps, SAST, signed releases.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>sign-artifacts.yml</code></td><td>release tag</td><td>Produces signed build provenance for published artifacts. Complements npm <code>--provenance</code> in <code>release-npm.yml</code>.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>fuzz.yml</code></td><td>push · PR · weekly Sat 08:00 UTC</td><td>atheris fuzzer against <code>tests/fuzz/fuzz_spending_policy.py</code>, capped at <code>FUZZING_DURATION=60</code>s for PRs.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Deploy workflows -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Deploy</div>
          <h2>Production deploys.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Workflow</th><th>Target</th><th>Path filter</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>deploy-api-cloudrun.yml</code></td>
              <td>Cloud Run · <code>us-east1</code> · service <code>sardis-api</code></td>
              <td><code>packages/sardis-api/**</code>, <code>sardis-core/**</code>, <code>sardis-chain/**</code></td>
              <td>GCP OIDC via Workload Identity Federation (no long-lived keys). Build through <code>cloudbuild.yaml</code>, deploy, then <code>curl /health</code> — non-200 fails the run. If <code>GCP_WORKLOAD_IDENTITY_PROVIDER</code> is missing, the job fails loudly with remediation instructions (previously silently skipped).</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>deploy-landing.yml</code></td>
              <td>Vercel · <code>sardis.sh</code></td>
              <td><code>apps/landing/**</code>, <code>pnpm-lock.yaml</code></td>
              <td>Build job (typecheck + lint + build) on every PR for preview. Deploy job is <code>if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main' &amp;&amp; github.event_name == 'push'</code> — prod only.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>deploy.yml</code></td>
              <td>(legacy orchestrator / retained)</td>
              <td>—</td>
              <td>Broad-spectrum deploy workflow kept for manual <code>workflow_dispatch</code> redeploys.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Deploy environment map -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Environments</div>
          <h2>Where each surface lives.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Surface</th><th>Provider</th><th>Project / service</th><th>Host</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>API (sardis-api)</td><td>Cloud Run</td><td>service <code>sardis-api</code> · region <code>us-east1</code></td><td>api.sardis.sh (via LB) · direct Cloud Run URL for health checks</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Landing</td><td>Vercel</td><td><code>VERCEL_PROJECT_ID_LANDING</code></td><td><code>sardis.sh</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Docs</td><td>Vercel / Pages</td><td>deployed via <code>docs.yml</code></td><td><code>sardis.sh/docs</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Release workflows -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Release</div>
          <h2>Publish to registries.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Workflow</th><th>Tag pattern</th><th>Registry</th><th>Guardrails</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>release-python-sdk.yml</code></td>
              <td><code>py-sdk-v*</code></td>
              <td>PyPI (or TestPyPI for <code>a</code>/<code>b</code>/<code>rc</code>)</td>
              <td>Verifies <code>pyproject.toml</code> + <code>__init__.py</code> versions match the tag. Runs <code>pytest</code>, <code>python -m build</code>, <code>twine check</code>, upload, then smoke-installs from the registry with 6-retry backoff.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>release-python-integrations.yml</code></td>
              <td><code>py-langchain-v*</code>, <code>py-crewai-v*</code>, <code>py-adk-v*</code>, <code>py-agent-sdk-v*</code>, <code>py-connect-v*</code></td>
              <td>PyPI / TestPyPI</td>
              <td>Same shape as sardis-sdk release: version consistency check, build, twine, upload, smoke install + import check.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>release-npm.yml</code></td>
              <td><code>mcp-v*</code>, <code>sdk-js-v*</code>, <code>ai-sdk-v*</code>, <code>connect-js-v*</code></td>
              <td>npm (<code>--access public --provenance</code>)</td>
              <td>Verifies <code>package.json</code> version, runs pnpm tests + typecheck + build, <code>npm pack --dry-run</code>, asserts built artifacts exist (<code>dist/index.js</code> / <code>dist/cli.js</code>), publishes with <code>next</code> or <code>latest</code> dist-tag, smoke installs via <code>npx</code> or dynamic <code>import()</code>.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr><td><code>publish.yml</code></td><td>manual + tags</td><td>npm / PyPI</td><td>Umbrella publish orchestrator.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>release-dry-run.yml</code></td><td>PR · workflow_dispatch</td><td>none</td><td>Dry-run of the whole release pipeline — builds, twine check, <code>npm pack --dry-run</code> — without publishing.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>sign-artifacts.yml</code></td><td>release tag</td><td>—</td><td>Signs built artifacts; npm provenance is already set on <code>release-npm.yml</code>.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Monitoring -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Monitoring</div>
          <h2>Synthetic checks from CI.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            GitHub Actions is cheap enough that we use it as a second uptime system alongside the
            application's own health endpoints. Failures Slack us.
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Workflow</th><th>Schedule</th><th>What it checks</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>monitoring.yml</code></td><td>every 10 min</td><td><code>GET /api/v2/health</code> — asserts 200 + payload <code>status in &#123;ok, healthy, partial&#125;</code>, warns if response time &gt; 2.0s, Slack-webhook notify on failure.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>uptime.yml</code></td><td>scheduled</td><td>Base uptime probe aggregated into the public status page.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>uptime-response-time.yml</code></td><td>scheduled</td><td>Records response-time histograms.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>uptime-graphs.yml</code></td><td>scheduled</td><td>Generates historical graphs rendered on the status site.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>uptime-static-site.yml</code></td><td>scheduled</td><td>Builds and publishes the static status site.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>uptime-summary.yml</code></td><td>scheduled</td><td>Rolls checks into the summary feed.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Nightly + Docs -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Nightly + Docs</div>
          <h2>Long-running and documentation pipelines.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title"><code>nightly-sandbox-e2e.yml</code></div>
            <div class="card-description">
              Runs 04:20 UTC. <code>bash scripts/ci/run_nightly_sandbox_smoke.sh</code> against
              <code>SARDIS_SANDBOX_BASE_URL</code>. Gated live E2E behind
              <code>RUN_LIVE_SANDBOX_TESTS=1</code> (set via <code>workflow_dispatch</code> input) —
              when enabled, exercises Stripe, Lithic, and Coinbase CDP with real sandbox credentials.
              45-minute timeout.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title"><code>docs.yml</code></div>
            <div class="card-description">
              Builds and deploys the documentation site on changes to <code>docs/</code>. Mirrors the
              Vercel shape of the public landing app: build on PR for preview, deploy on merge to <code>main</code>.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Gunicorn + deploy gotchas -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Gotchas</div>
          <h2>Deploy lessons paid for in incidents.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Things that silently failed at least once and now have permanent fixes in the deploy
            scripts. Worth knowing before you touch Cloud Run config.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Gunicorn 25.x — use call syntax, not <code>--factory</code></div>
            <div class="card-description">
              Launch the API as <code>"sardis_api.main:create_app()"</code>. The <code>--factory</code>
              flag was removed in gunicorn 25.x; using it produces a cryptic boot failure that looks
              like a module-not-found error. Both Docker <code>CMD</code> and
              <code>scripts/deploy-cloudrun.sh</code> encode the call form.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Install gunicorn + uvicorn inside <code>.venv</code></div>
            <div class="card-description">
              The container's system Python shouldn't host gunicorn — uv installs into <code>.venv</code>,
              so gunicorn must live there too. Otherwise Cloud Run boots with the wrong interpreter and
              the app never binds its port, tripping the startup probe.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Always <code>gcloud ... --update-env-vars</code>, never <code>--set-env-vars</code></div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>--set-env-vars</code> silently wipes every other env var on the service. Use
              <code>--update-env-vars</code> to merge. This is encoded in
              <code>scripts/deploy-cloudrun.sh</code> but matters every time someone pokes Cloud Run by hand.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Workload Identity Federation, not SA keys</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>deploy-api-cloudrun.yml</code> authenticates through
              <code>google-github-actions/auth</code> with
              <code>GCP_WORKLOAD_IDENTITY_PROVIDER</code> + <code>GCP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT</code>. No
              JSON key lives in GitHub secrets. If the WIF provider secret is missing, the job
              fails loudly (older behaviour silently skipped — backend changes never shipped for weeks).
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Cross-refs -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Go deeper</div>
          <h2>Related canvases.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <a class="canvas-card" href="/architecture">
            <div class="canvas-card-num">01 · System</div>
            <div class="canvas-card-title">Architecture Overview</div>
            <div class="canvas-card-desc">The seven-layer stack these pipelines deploy.</div>
          </a>
          <a class="canvas-card" href="/security">
            <div class="canvas-card-num">19 · Ops</div>
            <div class="canvas-card-title">Security Model</div>
            <div class="canvas-card-desc">Trust boundaries, fail-closed defaults, secret handling — all of which CI enforces.</div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
</Canvas>
